## 3. Finished hypnotic “Mission” script (you can drop into Max Briefings)

Use this as a template; tweak words to fit your brand voice.

***

**MISSION ACTIVATION SCRIPT – v1**

You are not just passing time; you are carrying a mission.  
There is something specific you want, something your life keeps circling back to, no matter how much you try to downplay it.

Why do you think this mission keeps returning to you?  
Of all the people on this planet, why did it land in your hands, on your heart, in your mind?  
What does it know about you that you sometimes forget about yourself?

You have already collected tools for this—skills, scars, stories, connections, moments you survived that other people would have folded under.  
You did not come this far empty-handed.  
You are more prepared than your fear wants you to believe.

Ask yourself quietly:  
What do I gain if I complete this mission… and what do I lose if I walk away?  
What happens to the people I love if I rise to this, and what happens to them if I stay the same?

Notice which answer hits harder in your chest.

Maybe you’re not afraid of the work.  
Maybe you’re afraid of the size of the life that waits on the other side of saying yes.

So let me ask you this:  
Are you willing to let your mission go unfinished just because the path is not perfectly lit?  
Or are you the kind of person who moves anyway, and lets the light catch up?

Today, you don’t have to complete the mission.  
You only have to act like someone who *accepts* it.  
Send the message. Write the plan. Take the small step that proves you’re serious.

Your mission chose you for a reason.  
Now you get to choose it back.

***

You can also do a shorter, **Max-style compressed version**:

> There is a mission with your name on it, and it has already watched you survive what should have broken you. It knows you’re qualified.  
> So ask yourself: what costs more—chasing what you really want, or living with the regret of never trying?  
> Today, you don’t need the whole roadmap. You just need one decisive step that proves you’re the kind of person who accepts their assignment.

